dismissalText.commentary: Will Young c Markram b Ngidi 21 (23b 3x4 0x6 35m) SR: 91.3

dismissalComment.html: Ngidi gets the breakthrough! The slower ball does the trick, rolling out an off-cutter that tempts Young into a full-blooded strike down the ground. The problem, however, is it sticks in the pitch and the ball ends up kissing the clouds before nestling safely in the hands of Markram stood still at mid off

dismissalText.commentary: Rachin Ravindra c Klaasen b Rabada 108 (101b 13x4 1x6 147m) SR: 106.93

dismissalComment.html: Edged and gone! Across Ravindra, pace off at 123.5kph, and an attempt to carve this over cover produces a thick outside edge, taken by Klaasen shuffling to his left. A gorgeous innings comes to an end, but New Zealand are in a strong position with plenty of explosiveness to come...

dismissalText.commentary: Ryan Rickelton c Bracewell b Henry 17 (12b 4x4 0x6 20m) SR: 141.66

dismissalComment.html: Held in the wicket, popped straight to cover. Rickelton was looking so good but falls early. 135ks length ball on fifth from Henry, looked innocuous and the batter was in a good position to punch it off the front foot. But the ball was released with a slight wobble, it landed on the seam and went off the outer-half of the bat, travelled 23 metres for Bracewell to take a low catch in front. Rickelton shakes his head while walking back; the fielders beam with smiles as they run about for hugs and cheers

Was a length ball that landed outside off and spun in to hit Jansen just under the knee-roll. On the left edge of the pad. His front foot had moved to fourth stump for the reverse sweep, that he missed completely. Beaten on the underedge. Haek-Eye shows it was a shortish ball on fourth stump, impact is on middle and off, and it's hitting leg!
